      <h2>Strictly forbidden foods</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Chocolate</strong> — toxic even in small quantities (theobromine)</li>
        <li><strong>Grapes & raisins</strong> — acute kidney failure; even a single grape can kill a small dog</li>
        <li><strong>Onion, garlic, shallot</strong> — red blood cell destruction</li>
        <li><strong>Xylitol</strong> (sweetener in chewing gums, some peanut butters) — sudden hypoglycaemia</li>
        <li><strong>Avocado</strong> — toxic persin compound</li>
        <li><strong>Cooked bones</strong> — shatter into splinters that can perforate the intestine</li>
        <li><strong>Macadamia nuts</strong> — temporary paralysis</li>
        <li><strong>Alcohol</strong> — obvious but worth stating</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Nordic breed specifics</h3>
      <p>Pomsky and Husky have an extraordinary metabolism — they can function on less food than their size suggests. An under-stimulated, over-fed Husky will gain weight quickly. Monitor body condition (ribs should be palpable but not visible) rather than fixating on bowl quantities.</p>
